> SELECT  id,item_name,item_code,store_id,status  FROM test_store_Item     WHERE (id IN (select id from test_store_Item where store_id = 1006) AND store_id IN (?))

@liquanjin Hi, what is the type of parameter in `store_id IN (?)`? 
The first parameter(`store_id=1006`) will be processed as int by default. If the second parameter(`store_id IN (?)`) type is different, it will cause an error in subquery check.

